The Chairman of Ikole Local Government Area in Ekiti State, Mr Sola Olominu, on Thursday, inaugurated the installation of 100 solar-powered street lights in Ikole Ekiti. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the solar-powered street light was installed in Oke Aremo Quarters of the town. “I am officially flagging the installation of 100 poles solar powered street lights along Ara Road in Oke Aremo Quarters in Ikole-Ekiti to keep the area safe at night in the name of God,” he said. NAN reports that the chairman also inspected the reconstruction of Ikole town. (NAN) 